rol}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thyagu}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tamil comedians]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:People from Thanjavur district]]\n[[Category:Indian male comedians]]\n[[Category:Tamil male actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Cleanup bare URLs|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Thyagu\n| image         =\n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = Thyagu at [[Manal Naharam]] audio launch\n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1958|2|05}}<ref>http://www.nettv4u.com/celebrity/tamil/movie-actor/thiyagu</ref>\n| birth_place   =Kumbakonam\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| othername     = \n| yearsactive   = 1980 - Present\n| spouse        =\n| website       = \n| notable role  = \n| occupation    = [[Film actor]]\n}}\n\n'''Thyagu'''  (born 2 February 1958) is a [[Tamil people|Tamil]] [[film actor]] who has appeared in comedy roles.<ref>http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/events/29678.html</ref><ref>http://entertainment.oneindia.in/celebs/thiyagu/filmography.html</ref> He has played various kind of roles in the Tamil film industry. He is the grandson of violinist [[Kumbakonam Rajamanickam Pillai]].<ref>http://ibnlive.in.com/news/thiyagu-quits-dmk-may-join-aiadmk/186746-60.html</ref>\n\n==Career==\nBeginning as a protagonist, Thyagu played roles in ''[[Oru Thalai Ragam]]'' and ''[[Palaivana Solai (1981 film)|Palaivana Solai]]'', before playing antagonistic roles in the late 1980s and early 1990s. In the 2000s, he often formed an association with Vadivelu and would appear in a few scenes in films he had signed for, occasionally portraying comedy roles. His recent work includes roles in ''[[Kuselan]]'' as well as a politician in the ''[[Singam]]'' series.\n\nIn 2011, Thyagu quit the DMK political party, whom he had been associated with for twenty-eight years.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/article365943.ece</ref> Soon after his split, he lamented the leader Karunanidhi's broken promise of honouring Thyagu's grandfather with a postage stamp as a reason of his departure.<ref>http://chennaionline.com/movies/cine-buzz/20112524052524/Thiyagu-quits-DMK-citing-shoddy-treatment.col</ref>\n\n== Selected filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"background:#f5f5f5;\"\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n!class=unsortable| Notes\n|-\n| 1980 || ''[[Oru Thalai Ragam]]'' || ||\n|-\n| 1981 || ''[[Palaivana Solai (1981 film)|Palaivana Solai]]'' || Siva ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 1982 || ''[[Kalyana Kalam]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Manjal Nila]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Chinna Marumagal]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Pakkathu Veetu Roja]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Agaya Gangai (film)|Aagaya Gangai]]'' || ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1985 || ''[[Annai Bhoomi 3D]]'' || Shankar ||\n|-\n| ''[[Idaya Kovil]]'' || Suresh's friend ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"| 1986 ||''[[Uyire Unakkaga]]'' || B\u00e2lu's friend ||\n|-\n| ''Jothi Malar'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Aayiram Pookkal Malarattum]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Oomai Vizhigal]]'' || Velu ||\n|-\n| ''[[Vidinja Kalyanam]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Oru Iniya Udhayam]]'' || ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\"| 1987 || ''[[Velicham]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Paruva Ragam]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Muthukkal Moondru]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ananda Aradhanai]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Cooliekkaran]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Veeran Veluthambi]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Jallikattu (1987 film)|Jallikattu]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Theertha Karaiyinile]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''Pasam Oru Vesam'' || ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\"| 1988 || ''[[Annanagar Mudhal Theru]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Therkathi Kallan]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''Oorai Therinjukithen'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Paasa Paravaigal]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Rayilukku Neramachu]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Poonthotta Kaavalkaaran]